### Blockchain and Cryptocurrency Risks

CRYPTOCURRENCY AND BLOCKCHAIN TECHNOLOGY INVOLVES SIGNIFICANT RISK. THIS
SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED FOR USE AT YOUR OWN RISK. THE AUTHORS AND COPYRIGHT
HOLDERS DISCLAIM ALL LIABILITY FOR ANY LOSSES, DAMAGES, OR CLAIMS ARISING
FROM USE OF THIS SOFTWARE OR THE SILVERBITCOIN BLOCKCHAIN NETWORK.

Users should:
- ✅ Understand blockchain technology before using
- ✅ Never invest more than they can afford to lose
- ✅ Keep private keys secure and backed up
- ✅ Comply with local laws and regulations
- ✅ Verify all transactions before confirming
- ✅ Conduct their own research (DYOR)
- ✅ Consult with financial advisors when appropriate

### Limitation of Liability

IN NO EVENT SHALL THE AUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT HOLDERS BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM,
DAMAGES OR OTHER LIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT OR
OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM, OUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE
USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE SOFTWARE.

This includes but is not limited to:
- Loss of funds or cryptocurrency
- Network downtime or failures
- Smart contract vulnerabilities
- Regulatory or legal issues
- Data loss or corruption
- Security breaches

